SUMMARY:[Maine Secretary of State] Maine Secretary of State’s Office ann
 ounces ranked choice tabulations
DESCRIPTION:AUGUSTA\, MAINE\n– The Elections division today completed ra
 nked choice tabulations on five June 9\, 2026 Primary Election races. Base
 d on ranked choice tabulations\, final results for each race are as follow
 s (Note: click the links for round-by-round details):\nGovernor – Republ
 ican\nWinner: Bobby Charles\nEliminated by round\n: 1-Libby\, 2-Wessels\, 
 3-Jones\, 4-McCarthy\, 5-Mason\, 6-Bush\nRunner-up Midgley\nGovernor – D
 emocrat\nWinner: Hannah Pingree\nEliminated by round\n: 1-King\, 2-Bellows
 \, 3-Jackson\nRunner-Up: Shah\nU.S. Congress CD2 – Democrat\nWinner: Mat
 thew Dunlap\nEliminated by round\n: 1-Loud\, 2-Wood\nRunner-Up: Baldacci\n
 Senate District 4 – Republican\n(Bradford\; Charleston\, Corinna\, Corin
 th\, Dexter\, Exeter\, Garland\, Glenburn\, Hudson\, Kenduskeag\, Levant)\
 nWinner: Chad Perkins\nEliminated by round\n: 1-Pierce\, 2-Wood\nRunner-Up
 : Guerin\nHouse District 58 – Republican\n(Belgrade\, Fayette\, Rome\, V
 ienna\, Mount Vernon\, New Sharon)\nWinner: Dexter Bridges\nEliminated by 
 round\n: 1-Harris\nRunner-up: Bessey\nIn Ranked Choice Voting races\, the 
 winner must receive a majority – more than 50% – of the vote. For more
  information about how ranked-choice races are tabulated\, visit the\nRCV 
 Resources webpage\n.\nRecount process:\nIn Ranked Choice Voting races\, on
 ly a candidate who received one of the top three rankings at the end of th
 e penultimate round of ranked‑choice counting may request a recount\, an
 d they must file with the Department of the Secretary of State a written r
 equest within five business days after results are announced. Maine statu
 te\nTitle 21-A\, §737-A\nlays out a specific plan\, process and any relat
 ed costs for votes to be recounted. In a recount\, representatives of each
  candidate and staff members from the Department of the Secretary of State
  manually review each paper ballot to determine the official vote tally.\n
 Results are unofficial until the official tabulation of the votes cast is 
 communicated to Governor Janet Mills. Official results will be available a
 nd posted on the\nElection Resu\nhttps://www.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secr
 etary-states-office-announces-ranked-choice-tabulations
URL:https://www.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secretary-states-office-announces
 -ranked-choice-tabulations
CATEGORIES:Maine Secretary of State
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
