SUMMARY:[Maine Secretary of State] Maine Secretary of State’s Office ann
 ounces recount schedule
DESCRIPTION:AUGUSTA\, MAINE\n– The Department of the Secretary of State 
 announced the schedule for recounts requested by candidates in three races
 :\nRecounts:\nMonday\, June 22 at 9 a.m.: Senate District 30 – Democrat\
 nThursday\, June 25 at 9 a.m.: House District 49 – Republican\nThursday\
 , June 25 at 1 p.m.: House District 135 – Democrat\nThe recounts will ta
 ke place in the Florian Room located at the Maine Public Safety Building a
 t 45 Commerce Ave.\, Augusta. Recounts are open to the public and media an
 d will be livestreamed on the Secretary of State’s\nYouTube page\n.\nAdd
 itional recounts could be requested following the conclusion of the ranked
  choice voting tabulations.\nRecount process:\nMaine statute\nTitle 21-A\,
  §737-A\nlays out a specific plan\, process and any related costs for vot
 es to be recounted. In a recount\, representatives of each candidate and s
 taff members from the Department of the Secretary of State manually review
  each paper ballot to determine the official vote tally:\nIn Ranked Choice
  Voting races\n: only a candidate who received one of the top three rankin
 gs at the end of the penultimate round of ranked‑choice counting may req
 uest a recount\, and they must file with the Secretary of State a written 
 request within five business days after results are announced.\nIn non-Ran
 ked Choice races:\nany candidate other than the apparent winner who desire
 s a recount must file with the Secretary of State a written request for a 
 recount within five business days after the election.\nOfficial results wi
 ll be available and posted within 20 days after the election on the\nElect
 ion Results page\n.\n###\nhttps://www.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secretary-s
 tates-office-announces-recount-schedule
URL:https://www.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secretary-states-office-announces
 -recount-schedule
CATEGORIES:Maine Secretary of State
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:82c68bb2f996f1d7@sos-corporations.maine-government-feeds
DTSTAMP:20260701T202233Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260616
SUMMARY:[Maine Secretary of State] Maine Secretary of State’s Office ann
 ounces additional races for Ranked Choice Voting tabulations\, recounts
DESCRIPTION:AUGUSTA\, MAINE\n– The Department of the Secretary of State 
 announced today two additional races will proceed to ranked choice voting 
 tabulation and three to recounts:\nRanked choice tabulation:\nHouse Distri
 ct 58 – Republican (Belgrade\, Fayette\, Rome\, Vienna\, Mount Vernon\, 
 New Sharon)\nSenate District 4 – Republican (Bradford\; Charleston\, Cor
 inna\, Corinth\, Dexter\, Exeter\, Garland\, Glenburn\, Hudson\, Kenduskea
 g\, Levant)\nGovernor – Democrat\nGovernor – Republican\nU.S. Congress
  CD2 – Democrat\nRecounts:\nSenate District 30 – Democrat (Gorham\, Sc
 arborough (part))\nHouse District 49 – Republican (Arrowsic\, Georgetown
 \, Phippsburg\, West Bath\, Woolwich)\nHouse District 135 – Democrat  (
 Kennebunk (part))\nThe ranked choice tabulation process began on Friday\, 
 June 12 at 1 PM at the Maine Department of Public Safety Headquarters buil
 ding located at 45 Commerce Drive in Augusta and is expected to conclude t
 his week. The ranked choice process is open to the public and media and is
  being livestreamed on the Secretary of State’s\nYouTube page\n. Recount
 s will begin next week with dates to be announced later this week.\nHow Ra
 nked Choice Voting works in Maine:\nIn Ranked Choice Voting races\, a cand
 idate must receive more than 50% of the first-choice votes as counted on E
 lection Day to win the race outright. If no candidate appears to have achi
 eved this based on initial unofficial results reports from the municipalit
 ies\, the Secretary of State’s Office makes the determination to proceed
  with the\nranked-choice voting tabulation\n. The votes are tabulated in 
 rounds\, with the lowest-ranked candidate eliminated in each round until t
 here are only two candidates remaining. The candidate determined to have r
 eceived the majority (more than 50%) of the votes in the final round is de
 clared the winner.  For more information about how ranked-choice races ar
 e tabulated\, visit the\nRCV Resources webpage\non the Secretary of State 
 website.\nRecount process:\nMaine statute\nTitle 21-A\, §737-A\nlays out 
 a specific plan\, \nhttps://www.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secretary-states-
 office-announces-additional-races-ranked-choice-voting-tabulations
URL:https://www.maine.gov/sos/news/maine-secretary-states-office-announces
 -additional-races-ranked-choice-voting-tabulations
CATEGORIES:Maine Secretary of State
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d3d6e01dd0ce5ba8@sos-corporations.maine-government-feeds
DTSTAMP:20260701T202233Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260611
SUMMARY:[Maine Secretary of State] Secretary of State issues decision in c
 hallenge to Kevin Nichols nomination petitions for Androscoggin County She
 riff
DESCRIPTION:AUGUSTA\, Maine\n— Secretary of State Shenna Bellows\nissued
  a decision\nregarding a challenge to the nomination petitions filed by Ke
 vin Nichols as a non-party candidate for Androscoggin County Sheriff.\nThe
  Secretary of State’s Office received the written challenge from Eric G.
  Samson alleging that Mr. Nichols has no recorded history of holding a sup
 ervisory position as required by Maine statute\n30-A M.R.S. §371-B (3)(E)
 \n. A hearing was held on Wednesday\, June 3 with Deputy Secretary Julie F
 lynn of the Bureau of Corporations\, Elections and Commissions serving as 
 the Presiding Officer at the Hearing\, and Assistant Attorney General Jon 
 Bolton assisting as legal counsel.\nThe Secretary\, upon review of the pro
 ceedings and evidence\, determined that Samson met his burden to establish
  that Nichols lacks the required supervisory employment experience.\n“Ba
 sed on the proceedings and the evidence\, I agree with the conclusion and 
 recommendation submitted by the hearings officer that Mr. Nichols lacks th
 e supervisory experience required by law to hold this position.”\nhttps:
 //www.maine.gov/sos/news/secretary-state-issues-decision-challenge-kevin-n
 ichols-nomination-petitions-androscoggin
URL:https://www.maine.gov/sos/news/secretary-state-issues-decision-challen
 ge-kevin-nichols-nomination-petitions-androscoggin
CATEGORIES:Maine Secretary of State
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
